    "description": "Juspay South Asia Partners invites applications from qualified candidates for the position of Financial Analyst at our Hyderabad location. This role offers excellent career advancement prospects.\n\nAbout Juspay South Asia Partners:\nJuspay South Asia Partners is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare annual reports and investor presentations\n• Prepare and analyze financial statements, reports, and budgets\n• Implement and maintain internal controls and audit procedures\n• Monitor market trends and provide investment recommendations\n• Process payroll and manage employee reimbursements\n• Monitor financial performance against targets and provide variance analysis\n• Liaise with banks, regulators, and financial institutions\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Master's degree preferred\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Tally\n• Proficiency in SAP FICO\n• Proficiency in Power BI\n• Proficiency in Financial Reporting\n• Proficiency in GST\n• Proficiency in Python for Finance\n• Proficiency in VBA\n• Proficiency in Financial Modeling\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Life and accident insurance\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Annual paid leaves and casual leaves\n• Flexible working hours\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Hyderabad, Telangana, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Juspay South Asia Partners!",
